<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100199433917002></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100199433917002><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100199433917002>RE: Best way from 1-55 as magi</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100199433917002#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Oct 1st 11:45 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;  After level 53, the seafuries get amazingly boring, and only teaming up with another mage could possibly make it better, more lucrative, or more interesting.  I did a duo with another magician to assist a druid in spawning and killing the corrupted clops, and for the fun of it we started chain pulling doubles.  We had tons of malachite, so resummoning wasn't an issue, and the druid cast a few dots here and there.  We had piles of cyclops corpses lying around, so when we finally had to take a mana break we also turned it into a loot break.  I made 800pp in less than 3 hours.<br><br>    On the other hand, with Kunark, you can solo in Burning Woods fairly well, and fairly safely.  An example would be the Forest Giant fort.  The Ancients can be blue all the way til 60, and the money is comparable to seafuries, plus there are occasionall spell drops.  Experience is more reliable here at 54 than in the Ocean of Tears.<br><br>    Fastest experience, though, would be in Seb or Velks groups.  Velks is easier, but Seb money/loot is better, and experience is comparable.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
